                        <interp inst="t18250519-89-victim523" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250519-89-off535 t18250519-89-victim523"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM JONES. I am a <rs id="t18250519-89-viclabel537" type="occupation">silk weaver</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250519-89-victim523 t18250519-89-viclabel537"></join>. On the 7th of May, about half-past nine o'clock in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18250519-89-crimeloc538">Wilson-street, Finsbury-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250519-89-crimeloc538" type="placeName" value="Wilson-street, Finsbury-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250519-89-crimeloc538" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250519-89-off535 t18250519-89-crimeloc538"></join> - my wife was with me: a young man came by, and took my watch from my fob - he ran away in a moment; I cannot tell who it was. I gave an alarm of Stop thief! and Mr. Fisher stopped the prisoner. I saw the case of my watch, but the inside of it was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250519-89-person524">
                  SAMUEL 
                  JOHN FISHER
               <interp inst="t18250519-89-person524" type="surname" value="JOHN FISHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250519-89-person524" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250519-89-person524" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going up Smith-street, and heard the cry of Stop thief! I made a start immediately, and saw a gentleman before me stop the prisoner; he was running, and fell down, when he was stopped - he said, "Don't stop me, I have only broken a window;" he was taken to the watch-house. I found this watch-case on the spot where he had fallen.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250519-89-person525">
                  THOMAS 
                  GOODING
               <interp inst="t18250519-89-person525" type="surname" value="GOODING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250519-89-person525" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250519-89-person525" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I heard the cry of Stop thief! and when I came up I saw the prisoner, and took him to the watch-house. Fisher showed me this watch-case afterwards.</p>
               <p>(Case produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I am innocent.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250519-89-verdict539" type="verdictDescription">
